info.description:
## What can I do? Perform money transfers to another member or merchant or even make donations by just **registering as a Member** to our service and verifying your mobile device as a trusted one. Once the registration step is completed simply **select the other member** you wish to **send money to or request money from or pay** and pretty much that's it. ## How do I register as a member? Simply invoke the /p2p/_**registerMember**_ and you are done. ## How do I send money? Once you have registered as a member find from your list of contacts the member you wish to send money or make a donation (e.g. Unicef). ## How do I request money? Simply invoke the /p2p/_**credit**_ and the other member can accept or reject it. ## How do I pay a merchant? The merchant will invoke the /p2p/_**machinePaymentRequestRegistration**_ and then the member can accept the payment by invoking the /p2p/_**acceptCredit**_ or reject it by invoking the /p2p/_**rejectCredit**_ . ## Sandbox Member Endpoints 1. _POST_ /p2p/_**registerMember**_ If you are not already registered to our service, invoke this endpoint to register. The mobile device registration is mandatory. 2. _POST_ /p2p/_**productList**_ Invoke this endpoint to find the list of your accounts and cards. 3. _POST_ /p2p/_**selectAccount**_ Invoke this endpoint to select the account you wish to use (e.g. an account or card). This is useful for the users that have registered as members with more then one account. 4. _POST_ /p2p/_**discoverMemberV2**_ Invoke this endpoint to search for members by supplying their network id (e.g. mobile phone number) 5. _POST_ /p2p/_**payV2**_ Invoke this endpoint to make a payment to another member. 6. _POST_ /p2p/_**credit**_ Invoke this endpoint to make a request to another member to send you money. 7. _POST_ /p2p/_**acceptCredit**_ Invoke this endpoint to accept another's member request to send him money (or approve a merchant payment) 8. _POST_ /p2p/_**rejectCredit**_ Invoke this endpoint to reject another's member request to send him money 9. _POST_ /p2p/_**walletTransactionList**_ Invoke this endpoint to get the list of your transactions 10. _POST_ /p2p/_**disableMember**_ Invoke this endpoint to deactivate yourself as member ## Sandbox Merchant Endpoints: 1. _POST_ /p2b/_**machinePaymentRequestRegistration**_ Invoke this endpoint to create a payment request as a merchant 2. _POSt_ /p2b/_**machinePaymentRequestInfo**_ Invoke this endpoint to get the status of the payment request ## Getting Started with the Sandbox 1. **Create your first Sandbox Application** Create a new Sandbox application by invoking the _POST_ /_**sandbox**_. This call will generate a new Sandbox with a unique sandbox_id , application_id and a user_id. IDs are UUIDs.
_**Important!**_ _Before proceeding save the sandbox id you just created._ 2. **Create your Sandbox Users** After creating your sandbox application, administrators may create users using POST /sandbox/_**{sandbox_id}/users**_.
